      %h2.article-main-title Headaches
      .article-main-content
        %p There are many different types of headaches: Migraines, Tension Headaches, Cluster Headaches, Occipital Neuralgia, Paroxysmal Hemicrania, etc. Each has a different presentation than the next, with specific telltale signs/symptoms and equally different treatments. The key to managing the symptoms of a headache lies in making a proper diagnosis. The causes of headaches are poorly understood, but advances in treatments and medication have allow countless headache suffers to lead normal lives.

